metadata.name: Disappointment
metadata.description:
It is a work that speaks of the pain of words and more so when they come from close people, when the family leaves you wounded. He talks about the importance of taking care of what we say because we never know how much damage our words can do. All the time talking about us about what we don't do or do, there will always be people who will talk, however, we decide how much we let it affect us and how much it hurts us. It is difficult to give way and continue, however, it is the best thing to not stagnate.

No commercial use rights given.
